Alistair Hey, a 57-year-old man who lives in a plush Queenstown neighbourhood in New Zealand, was sentenced to 70 hours of community work last week in the Invercargill District Court for assaulting his neighbour Tim Clark with weed killer last month. 

The whole thing was caught on CCTV cameras and Hey was  ordered to pay Clark $1500 in damages.

