The neighbours came to a head on September 14, when Clark's wife became distressed due to the continuous loud music coming from Hey's house, which had been playing for two days straight.    

'I called the council number and they sent an Armourguard guy to listen at seven or eight in the morning,' Clark told Stuff.co.nz.

'He noted that it was on and it was annoying and objectionable but Alistair wasn't there. He wasn't even in the house.

